  "notes": "Khmer (Cambodian) abugida. Two consonant series (first/second class) affect vowel quality. ប = implosive /ɓ/. No tonal system (unlike neighboring SE Asian languages). Vowel symbols combine with consonant class to yield different phonemes. This spec gives first-class consonant readings; second-class shifts vowels. Final consonants are unreleased.",
